'''Corbio''' was an ancient town of [[Latium]] in central [[Italy]].

In around 488 BC, Corbio was captured by an invading army of the [[Volsci]], led by [[Gaius Marcius Coriolanus]] and [[Attius Tullus Aufidius]].<ref>[[Livy]], ''[[Ab urbe condita (book)|Ab urbe condita]]'', 2.39</ref>

