{{Infobox Political post |post = President |body = the [[Tasmanian Legislative Council|Legislative Council]] |nativename = |insignia = Tasmania Coat of Arms.svg |insigniasize = |insigniacaption = |department = |image = |alt = |incumbent = [[Jim Wilkinson (Australian politician)|Jim Wilkinson]] |incumbentsince = 21 May 2013 |style = |residence = |nominator = |nominatorpost = |appointer = Elected by the [[Tasmanian Legislative Council]] |appointerpost = |termlength = |inaugural = [[Thomas Horne (politician)|Thomas Horne]] |formation = 2 December 1856 |last = |abolished = |succession = |deputy = [[Greg Hall (politician)|Greg Hall]] |salary = |website = }} The '''President of the Tasmanian Legislative Council''' is the presiding officer of the [[Tasmanian Legislative Council|Council]]. The current President is [[Jim Wilkinson (Australian politician)|Jim Wilkinson]] MLC who has presided over the Council since 21 May 2013.
